==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mancus
<hw>Man"cus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.]</ety> <def>An
old Anglo Saxon coin both of gold and silver, and of variously estimated
values. The silver <ex>mancus</ex> was equal to about one shilling of
modern English money.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>-mancy</ent>⟦br⟧
